# Git hygiene

## Branching

- **Never commit directly to `main`.** All work happens on a feature branch.
- Before starting implementation, create and switch to a branch:
  - `feature/<short-description>` for new work
  - `fix/<short-description>` for bug fixes
- If you are already on `main` with local changes, create the feature branch immediately (`git checkout -b …`) before committing.
- Keep branches focused: one feature or fix per branch / PR.

## Pull requests

- Open a PR into `main` when the work is ready for review (do not merge your own PR unless the user asks).
- PR title: concise, imperative, focused on why.
- PR body: short summary + test plan checklist.
- Do not push `--force` to `main` / `master`.

## Commits

- Commit on the feature branch only.
- Only commit when the user asks (existing user preference still applies).
- Never skip hooks (`--no-verify`) unless the user explicitly requests it.
